# `integration/phaser`

`golem-phaser` publishes the Phaser 4 helper package. It depends on `golem-engine` as the protocol/client runtime and should not duplicate JS transport, protobuf, or generated-manager behavior. Its `dist/` output is generated by `npm run build`/`npm prepack` and should not be hand-edited or committed.

The `phaser` codegen integration emits one raw `GolemPhaser.ts` registry module from `codegen/templates/phaser/`. There is intentionally no `tsc` finalizer here; the consumer game's bundler compiles it alongside game code.

`GolemPlugin` is a global Phaser plugin mapped as `this.golem`. It builds one generated client for the game, reconnects unexpected drops with game-lifetime timers, and disconnects only when explicitly requested or when the plugin/game is destroyed. Connection status is exposed through typed unsubscribeable notifications; game code owns connection UI.

Generated `defineEntityViews` builders require one `prefab`, `sprite`, `gpu`, or explicit `headless` definition for every schema entity. Generated registrations discriminate synchronized entity classes and wire typed entity-targeted events without placing Phaser state on those entities.

`EntityViewMount` owns scene-local presentation. Mounts subscribe to entity/event managers, backfill entities already present in `getAll()`, and destroy only views and subscriptions on scene shutdown. Synchronized models and the connection survive scene transitions, and multiple scenes may mount independent registries against the same client.

Prefab definitions accept any typed Phaser GameObject, including Phaser Editor-generated classes and Containers. Sprite definitions preserve duration-based interpolation, frame/custom synchronization, and `externalPosition` prediction bypass. GPU definitions create a scene-local `SpriteGpuEntityPool`; pools require WebGL, preallocate hidden members, keep stable entity slots, batch changes at `PRE_RENDER`, and hide/reuse removed slots.

`loadTiledMap` is the low-level scene loader for Tiled map URLs, parsed objects, or embedded UTF-8 JSON bytes. `loadTiledWorld` is the higher-level world-update helper: it resolves generated `mapUrl`/`tileData`, loads or reuses configured tileset textures, creates tile layers with `auto` GPU selection by default, and owns replacement, refresh, and teardown for a scene/key mount. Keep cache checks and Phaser loader event handling explicit so callers can use both helpers from generated world update callbacks without managing loader state themselves.
